# Citation Standards

When you present information gathered from Linkup:

## Inline citations

- Every factual claim must carry an inline citation as a markdown link: `[Source Title](URL)`.
- Only cite URLs that appear in the Linkup output — never invent, guess, or reconstruct a URL.
- Do not leave any fact, number, name, or date uncited.

## Response structure

- Lead with the key answer or finding.
- Include specific facts, figures, and dates.
- Organize by theme when covering multiple topics.

## Sources section

End every web-sourced response with a `Sources` section listing each URL referenced, with a date when available:

```
Sources:
- [Source Title](https://example.com/article) (Feb 2026)
- [Another Source](https://example.com/other) (Jan 2026)
```

This section is mandatory for web-sourced answers. If a claim cannot be backed by a returned source, state that it is unverified rather than presenting it as fact.
